@page
@model QRStickers.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Privacy Notice:</strong> Please review our privacy policy below. For questions about data handling, contact support.
</div>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We collect information that you provide directly to us, including:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Account registration information (email address, password)</li>
    <li>Optional profile information (display name)</li>
    <li>OAuth tokens for connected third-party services (e.g., Cisco Meraki)</li>
    <li>Usage data and application logs</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our services</li>
    <li>Authenticate users and secure accounts</li>
    <li>Connect to third-party services on your behalf</li>
    <li>Monitor and analyze usage patterns</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
<p>Your data is stored securely using industry-standard practices:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Passwords are hashed using ASP.NET Identity (bcrypt)</li>
    <li>OAuth tokens are encrypted at rest in Azure SQL Database</li>
    <li>All connections use HTTPS/TLS encryption</li>
    <li>Database access uses managed identity (passwordless authentication)</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>When you connect third-party services (e.g., Cisco Meraki), we:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Request only the minimum required permissions</li>
    <li>Store OAuth tokens securely in our database</li>
    <li>Cache organization, network, and device data locally</li>
    <li>Never share your credentials with other users or services</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
<p>We use cookies for:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Authentication (ASP.NET Identity authentication cookies)</li>
    <li>Session management</li>
    <li>Security (anti-forgery tokens)</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
<p>We retain your data for as long as your account is active. You may delete your account at any time, which will remove all associated data.</p>

<h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You have the right to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Access your personal data</li>
    <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
    <li>Delete your account and associated data</li>
    <li>Revoke third-party service connections</li>
</ul>

<h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify users of any material changes by posting the new policy on this page.</p>

<h2>9. Contact</h2>
<p>For questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact the project maintainers via GitHub.</p>

